VI'm an astrobiologist.
p11
aVI try to understand the origin of life on Earth
p12
aVand the possibilities of finding life
p13
aVelsewhere in the universe.
p14
aVPeople sometimes ask me,
p15
aVhow can you be an astrobiologist
p16
aVif you don't have your own spaceship?
p17
aa(lp18
VWell, what I do is that I study life
p19
aVin those environments on Earth
p20
aVthat most closely resemble other interesting places in the universe.
p21
aVAll life on Earth requires water,
p22
aVso in my case I focus on the intimate relationship
p23
aVbetween water and life
p24
aVin order to understand
p25
aVif we could find life in a planet as dry as Mars.
p26
aVBut since I do not have the 2.5 billion dollars
p27
aVto send my own robot to Mars,
