aa(lp31
VLocated in northern Chile,
p32
aVit is the oldest and driest desert on Earth.
p33
aVTo give you an idea of how dry it is,
p34
aVconsider here in Vancouver it rains over 1,000 millimeters of rain every year.
p35
aVIn the Atacama, there are places with no reported rains
p36
aVin the last 400 years.
