aa(lp49
VOne of my first findings was in the entrance of a cave
p50
aVfacing the Pacific Ocean.
p51
aVIn this place, we reported a new type of microalgae
p52
aVthat grew only on top of the spiderwebs that covered the cave entrance.
p53
aVHave you ever seen a spiderweb early in the morning?
p54
aVIt's covered with dew,
p55
aVso this microalgae learned that in order to carry photosynthesis
p56
aVin the coast of the driest desert on Earth,
p57
aVthey could use the spiderwebs.
